==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wey
<hw>Wey</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>weye</ets>, AS.
<ets>w<?/ge</ets> weight. <?/<?/<?/<?/. See <er>Weight</er>.]</ety>
<def>A certain measure of weight.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A
<xex>weye</xex> of Essex cheese.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Piers
Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A <xex>wey</xex> is 6<?/ tods, or 182 pounds, of wool; a
load, or five quarters, of wheat, 40 bushels of salt, each weighing 56
pounds; 32 cloves of cheese, each weighing seven pounds; 48 bushels of
oats and barley; and from two cwt. to three cwt. of butter.</note>
<rj><au>Simmonds.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

